Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}; dry thoroughly with #paper towels{}. Trim, peel, and quarter @carrot{3%ounce} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; finely chop leaves. Place @golden raisins{1%ounce} in a small #bowl{} with enough hot water to just cover.

Toss chickpeas on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{5%teaspoon}, half the @curry powder{1%tablespoon} (you'll use more in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until crispy, ~{18-20%minutes}. (It's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit as they roast.)

While chickpeas roast, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #pot{} over high heat. Add carrot and ¼ tsp curry powder (½ tsp for 4). (You'll use the rest of the curry powder in the next step.) Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 1 cup water (1¾ cups for 4), @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine juice from three lemon wedges and @sugar{1%teaspoon} (six wedges and 2 tsp sugar for 4 servings); stir to dissolve. Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} and 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4); season with salt and pepper. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Set aside, tossing occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{6%tablespoon}, lemon zest, remaining curry powder, and juice from remaining lemon. Season with salt and pepper. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan, skin sides down. Cook until skin is crisp and fish is almost cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is opaque and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add kale and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. Remove from heat.

> Use pan used for salmon here.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with kale, pickled cabbage (draining first), and chickpeas in separate sections. Drain and sprinkle raisins (roughly chopping first if desired) over top. Drizzle with dressing and serve.

Top bowls with salmon.